{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01B1Gh7jDUC1um7z7R23cNBj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Rw6GcyvhHJpomNttcuBjLN","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# RabbitMQ Upgrade & Configuration Migration Plan\n\n**Namespace:** `karma-rabbitmq-change-plan-only-20260-a643e83c`\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-18\n**Status:** PLAN ONLY — nothing in this document has been applied. The live\ncluster remains exactly as found.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State (as inspected)\n\n### Platform\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Image | `rabbitmq:3.12-management` |\n| RabbitMQ version | 3.12.14 (all 3 nodes) |\n| Erlang/OTP | 25.3.2.15 (erts 13.2.2.11) |\n| Topology | StatefulSet `rabbitmq`, 3 disk nodes, all Running/Ready |\n| Cluster | `rabbitmq-0/1/2.rabbitmq-headless...`, no alarms, no partitions |\n| Peer discovery | `rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s` (hostname address type) |\n| Partition handling | `cluster_partition_handling = pause_minority` |\n| Master locator | `queue_master_locator = min-masters` |\n| Plugins | `rabbitmq_management`, `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s` |\n| Resource requests/limits | none set on the container |\n\n### vhosts\n- `/` (default)\n- `/app`\n\n### Users & tags\n| User | Tags |\n|------|------|\n| `admin` | administrator |\n| `app-user` | (none) |\n\n### Permissions\n| vhost | user | configure | write | read |\n|-------|------|-----------|-------|------|\n| `/` | admin | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| `/app` | admin | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n| `/app` | app-user | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |\n\n### Policies / parameters\n- Policies: **none** defined on `/` or `/app` (user or operator).\n- Runtime parameters: **none** per-vhost.\n- Global parameters: only `internal_cluster_id` (system-managed).\n\n### Queues\n| vhost | queue | type | durable | arguments |\n|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | (none) |\n| `/` | (none) | | | |\n\n### Notable feature flags (all enabled)\n`quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`,\n`classic_queue_type_delivery_support`, `user_limits`, `feature_flags_v2`,\n`maintenance_mode_status`, plus the standard 3.12 set.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Upgrade Target & Rationale\n\nRecommend a **two-step major upgrade**: 3.12.14 → latest 3.13.x → 4.0.x.\nRabbitMQ does not support skipping a minor series for online/rolling upgrades,\nso 3.12 → 3.13 must precede any move to 4.x.\n\n| Step | From | To | Why |\n|------|------|----|----|\n| 1 | 3.12.14 | latest 3.13.x | Required stepping stone; enables Khepri preview, surfaces 4.0 deprecation warnings. |\n| 2 | 3.13.x | latest 4.0.x | Target release; classic mirrored queues fully removed, `queue_master_locator` removed. |\n\n### Compatibility blockers to resolve BEFORE step 2 (4.0)\n1. **Classic mirrored queues are removed in 4.0.** None are currently in use\n   (no HA policy, `app-queue` is plain classic), but the\n   `classic_mirrored_queue_version` flag is enabled. Confirm no mirrored queues\n   exist at change time and migrate any to **quorum queues**.\n2. **`queue_master_locator` is removed in 4.0**, replaced by\n   `queue_leader_locator` (`balanced` / `client-local`). Update\n   `rabbitmq-config` accordingly (`queue_leader_locator = balanced`).\n3. **Erlang version:** 4.0 requires Erlang 26+. The `rabbitmq:4.0-management`\n   image bundles a compatible OTP, so this is handled by the image bump.\n4. **Feature flags:** all required flags must be `enabled` (not just\n   `enabled`/`disabled` mix) before each upgrade. Current set is fully enabled —\n   re-verify after step 1 and run `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Configuration Migration Items\n\n| Current | Action in change window | Notes |\n|---------|------------------------|-------|\n| `app-queue` (classic, durable) | Evaluate migration to **quorum queue** | Quorum queues require redeclaration; cannot convert in place. Plan a drain → redeclare → repoint clients, or use a shadow queue + cutover. |\n| No HA policy | Add quorum-queue-based redundancy policy if HA is desired | Do NOT add classic mirroring (deprecated/removed). |\n| `app-user` permissions `.* .* .*` on `/app` | Tighten to least privilege | Optional hardening; restrict configure/write/read regexes to the resources the app actually needs. |\n| `queue_master_locator = min-masters` | Replace with `queue_leader_locator = balanced` | Do at the 3.13→4.0 step. |\n| No resource requests/limits | Set CPU/memory requests + limits on the STS | Improves scheduling/QoS stability during rolling restarts. |\n| No memory/disk watermark tuning | Review `vm_memory_high_watermark` | Defaults acceptable; revisit under load. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Execution Procedure (for the scheduled change window)\n\nRolling, one node at a time, oldest ordinal last (StatefulSet updates highest\nordinal first; rely on `OnDelete` or controlled `RollingUpdate`).\n\n1. **Pre-checks**\n   - `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` — 3/3 running, no alarms, no partitions.\n   - `rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app` — confirm queue types; back up definitions.\n   - Export definitions: `rabbitmqadmin export definitions.json` (or\n     `rabbitmqctl export_definitions`). Store off-cluster.\n   - Verify all feature flags enabled.\n2. **Bump image** in StatefulSet from `rabbitmq:3.12-management` to the 3.13\n   target (step 1), later to `rabbitmq:4.0-management` (step 2).\n3. **Rolling restart**: for each node, put into maintenance\n   (`rabbitmqctl drain` / `upgrade drain`), wait for it to be removed from\n   serving, let the pod restart on the new image, wait until it rejoins and is\n   fully synced (`rabbitmqctl await_online_quorum_plus_one` / check\n   `cluster_status`) before proceeding to the next.\n4. **Post step-1**: `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`; verify no 4.0\n   deprecation warnings in logs.\n5. **Between steps**: update `rabbitmq-config` (`queue_leader_locator`), migrate\n   `app-queue` to quorum if chosen, apply any new policies.\n6. **Step 2 (4.0)**: repeat image bump + rolling restart.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Validation (post-upgrade)\n\n- `rabbitmqctl status` on each node → expected version, no errors.\n- `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` → 3 running nodes, no partitions, no alarms.\n- `rabbitmqctl list_vhosts` → `/`, `/app` present.\n- `rabbitmqctl list_users` → `admin` (administrator), `app-user`.\n- `rabbitmqctl list_permissions -p /app` → unchanged (or tightened per plan).\n- `rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app` → `app-queue` present and reachable.\n- Publish/consume smoke test against `/app` with `app-user`.\n- Management UI (port 15672) reachable; `loopback_users.guest = false` honored.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Rollback\n\n- **Definitions backup** taken in step 1 is the recovery artifact.\n- Single-step (3.13) rollback: RabbitMQ does **not** support in-place\n  downgrade. Rollback = redeploy previous image on a fresh data dir and import\n  the exported definitions; or restore from a volume snapshot taken\n  pre-upgrade.\n- **Take a PV/volume snapshot of all three `rabbitmq-N` PVCs immediately before\n  each step** — this is the only reliable rollback for mnesia/Khepri state.\n- Abort criteria: a node fails to rejoin within the SLA, persistent partition,\n  or queue data loss → halt, restore snapshot, re-import definitions.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|\n| Skipping 3.13 → unsupported 3.12→4.0 jump | Enforce two-step path. |\n| Classic→quorum migration drops messages | Drain queue first; shadow-queue cutover; schedule during low traffic. |\n| No resource limits → OOM during rolling restart | Set requests/limits before the window. |\n| Downgrade impossible | PV snapshots + definitions export before every step. |\n| Feature flags not fully enabled blocks upgrade | `enable_feature_flag all` and verify pre-step. |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":379,"cache_read_input_tokens":33921,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":379},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7dd8751a-4886-4695-973a-3ecf442615ce","uuid":"f6df3170-84f3-4f9d-ba3e-4853c38d1801","request_id":"req_011CcAXVxMo3CgQXLXnDvikq"}
