{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019KozJA5YtGUjQ772fSa2zM","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# spark-pi Namespace — Migration & Upgrade Change Plan\n2\t\n3\tStatus: DRAFT FOR REVIEW — no changes have been applied. Live configuration is\n4\tunchanged. Execution is deferred to an approved change window.\n5\t\n6\tDate: 2026-06-18  |  Scope: namespace spark-pi  |  Author: ops migration prep\n7\t\n8\t---\n9\t\n10\t## 1. Current State (baseline, as inspected)\n11\t\n12\tWorkloads (all on image apache/spark:3.5.3, ServiceAccount spark-pi):\n13\t\n14\t- spark-master (Deployment): replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi; ports 7077,8080.\n15\t- spark-worker (Deployment): replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi;\n16\t  env SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1.\n17\t- spark-pi (Job): spark-submit --master local[2] --driver-memory 512m,\n18\t  SparkPi partitions=1000, backoffLimit=0 (currently Completed).\n19\t\n20\tRBAC: Role spark-pi-role (LIVE verbs create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on\n21\tservices, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, AND pods), RoleBinding\n22\tspark-pi-role-binding -> SA spark-pi. SA \"default\" exists but is unused.\n23\t\n24\tConfigMaps: kube-root-ca.crt (system), config-audit (prior read-only audit).\n25\tNetworkPolicies: none. securityContext: {} (empty) on all workloads.\n26\t\n27\tCarried findings from config-audit: F1 securityContext hardening missing (HIGH),\n28\tF2 RBAC over-permission + drift on \"pods\" (MEDIUM), F3 no NetworkPolicy (MEDIUM),\n29\tF4 mutable image tag / no digest pin (LOW).\n30\t\n31\t---\n32\t\n33\t## 2. Planned Changes (what to change)\n34\t\n35\tC1 [Upgrade/F4] Bump apache/spark:3.5.3 -> next approved patch (latest 3.5.x),\n36\t   pinned by digest @sha256:... Apply uniformly to master, worker, and Job template.\n37\tC2 [Security/F1] Add restricted securityContext to all three workloads:\n38\t   runAsNonRoot: true, runAsUser: <non-zero>, allowPrivilegeEscalation: false,\n39\t   readOnlyRootFilesystem: true (emptyDir for /tmp + spark work dirs),\n40\t   capabilities.drop: [ALL], seccompProfile.type: RuntimeDefault.\n41\tC3 [RBAC/F2] Reconcile Role to declared manifest: remove out-of-band \"pods\" and\n42\t   trim write verbs (delete/update/patch) not needed by the SparkPi batch job;\n43\t   re-apply from version control to stop drift.\n44\tC4 [Network/F3] Add default-deny NetworkPolicy + explicit allows for\n45\t   worker->master 7077 and operator access to UI 8080/8081.\n46\tC5 [Hygiene] Set automountServiceAccountToken: false where the token is not\n47\t   needed; confirm unused \"default\" SA stays unused.\n48\t\n49\t---\n50\t\n51\t## 3. Order of Execution (lowest-risk first)\n52\t\n53\t1. C4 NetworkPolicy (additive; apply default-deny last) — validate connectivity.\n54\t2. C3 RBAC reconcile — confirm Job still runs under reduced permissions.\n55\t3. C2 securityContext hardening — rolling restart of master/worker.\n56\t4. C1 image upgrade — rolling update master/worker, then re-run Job.\n57\t5. C5 SA token hygiene — final tightening.\n58\t\n59\tRationale: apply isolation and least-privilege before the version bump so the\n60\tupgrade is validated against the hardened baseline; keep the version change last\n61\tand easiest to roll back.\n62\t\n63\t---\n64\t\n65\t## 4. Verification Per Step\n66\t\n67\t- C4: kubectl get netpol -n spark-pi; worker logs show registration to\n68\t  spark://spark-master:7077; master 8080 UI reachable only from allowed source.\n69\t- C3: kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi <verb> <res>\n70\t  -n spark-pi matches intended matrix; re-run Job -> Completed.\n71\t- C2: kubectl get pod -o jsonpath shows runAsNonRoot/dropped caps; pods Running 1/1;\n72\t  no CrashLoop.\n73\t- C1: kubectl get deploy -o jsonpath='{..image}' shows new digest; kubectl rollout\n74\t  status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi; re-run spark-pi Job,\n75\t  expect log \"Pi is roughly 3.14...\" and exit 0.\n76\t\n77\t---\n78\t\n79\t## 5. Rollback\n80\t\n81\tEach change applied from version-controlled manifests; rollback = kubectl rollout\n82\tundo (deployments) or re-apply previous manifest (Role, NetworkPolicy, Job). Take a\n83\tkubectl get all,role,rolebinding,netpol -o yaml snapshot before the window.\n84\tbackoffLimit=0 means a failed verification Job run must be deleted and re-created,\n85\tnot auto-retried.\n86\t\n87\t---\n88\t\n89\t## 6. Approval\n90\t\n91\tThis plan must be reviewed and signed off before any kubectl apply is executed.\n92\tNo item above has been applied; the live spark-pi namespace remains exactly as\n93\tinspected on 2026-06-18.\n94\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7dd8751a-4886-4695-973a-3ecf442615ce","uuid":"2936fa30-6bd3-4459-8235-0407b6f20441","timestamp":"2026-06-18T09:58:17.558Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# spark-pi Namespace — Migration & Upgrade Change Plan\n\nStatus: DRAFT FOR REVIEW — no changes have been applied. Live configuration is\nunchanged. Execution is deferred to an approved change window.\n\nDate: 2026-06-18  |  Scope: namespace spark-pi  |  Author: ops migration prep\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State (baseline, as inspected)\n\nWorkloads (all on image apache/spark:3.5.3, ServiceAccount spark-pi):\n\n- spark-master (Deployment): replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi; ports 7077,8080.\n- spark-worker (Deployment): replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi;\n  env SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1.\n- spark-pi (Job): spark-submit --master local[2] --driver-memory 512m,\n  SparkPi partitions=1000, backoffLimit=0 (currently Completed).\n\nRBAC: Role spark-pi-role (LIVE verbs create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on\nservices, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, AND pods), RoleBinding\nspark-pi-role-binding -> SA spark-pi. SA \"default\" exists but is unused.\n\nConfigMaps: kube-root-ca.crt (system), config-audit (prior read-only audit).\nNetworkPolicies: none. securityContext: {} (empty) on all workloads.\n\nCarried findings from config-audit: F1 securityContext hardening missing (HIGH),\nF2 RBAC over-permission + drift on \"pods\" (MEDIUM), F3 no NetworkPolicy (MEDIUM),\nF4 mutable image tag / no digest pin (LOW).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Planned Changes (what to change)\n\nC1 [Upgrade/F4] Bump apache/spark:3.5.3 -> next approved patch (latest 3.5.x),\n   pinned by digest @sha256:... Apply uniformly to master, worker, and Job template.\nC2 [Security/F1] Add restricted securityContext to all three workloads:\n   runAsNonRoot: true, runAsUser: <non-zero>, allowPrivilegeEscalation: false,\n   readOnlyRootFilesystem: true (emptyDir for /tmp + spark work dirs),\n   capabilities.drop: [ALL], seccompProfile.type: RuntimeDefault.\nC3 [RBAC/F2] Reconcile Role to declared manifest: remove out-of-band \"pods\" and\n   trim write verbs (delete/update/patch) not needed by the SparkPi batch job;\n   re-apply from version control to stop drift.\nC4 [Network/F3] Add default-deny NetworkPolicy + explicit allows for\n   worker->master 7077 and operator access to UI 8080/8081.\nC5 [Hygiene] Set automountServiceAccountToken: false where the token is not\n   needed; confirm unused \"default\" SA stays unused.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Order of Execution (lowest-risk first)\n\n1. C4 NetworkPolicy (additive; apply default-deny last) — validate connectivity.\n2. C3 RBAC reconcile — confirm Job still runs under reduced permissions.\n3. C2 securityContext hardening — rolling restart of master/worker.\n4. C1 image upgrade — rolling update master/worker, then re-run Job.\n5. C5 SA token hygiene — final tightening.\n\nRationale: apply isolation and least-privilege before the version bump so the\nupgrade is validated against the hardened baseline; keep the version change last\nand easiest to roll back.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Verification Per Step\n\n- C4: kubectl get netpol -n spark-pi; worker logs show registration to\n  spark://spark-master:7077; master 8080 UI reachable only from allowed source.\n- C3: kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi <verb> <res>\n  -n spark-pi matches intended matrix; re-run Job -> Completed.\n- C2: kubectl get pod -o jsonpath shows runAsNonRoot/dropped caps; pods Running 1/1;\n  no CrashLoop.\n- C1: kubectl get deploy -o jsonpath='{..image}' shows new digest; kubectl rollout\n  status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi; re-run spark-pi Job,\n  expect log \"Pi is roughly 3.14...\" and exit 0.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback\n\nEach change applied from version-controlled manifests; rollback = kubectl rollout\nundo (deployments) or re-apply previous manifest (Role, NetworkPolicy, Job). Take a\nkubectl get all,role,rolebinding,netpol -o yaml snapshot before the window.\nbackoffLimit=0 means a failed verification Job run must be deleted and re-created,\nnot auto-retried.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Approval\n\nThis plan must be reviewed and signed off before any kubectl apply is executed.\nNo item above has been applied; the live spark-pi namespace remains exactly as\ninspected on 2026-06-18.\n","numLines":94,"startLine":1,"totalLines":94}}}
