spark-pi-role-binding -> SA spark-pi. SA \"default\" exists but is unused.","+### Users & tags","+| User | Tags |","+|------|------|","+| `admin` | administrator |","+| `app-user` | (none) |"," ","-ConfigMaps: kube-root-ca.crt (system), config-audit (prior read-only audit).","-NetworkPolicies: none. securityContext: {} (empty) on all workloads.","+### Permissions","+| vhost | user | configure | write | read |","+|-------|------|-----------|-------|------|","+| `/` | admin | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |","+| `/app` | admin | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |","+| `/app` | app-user | `.*` | `.*` | `.*` |"," ","-Carried findings from config-audit: F1 securityContext hardening missing (HIGH),","-F2 RBAC over-permission + drift on \"pods\" (MEDIUM), F3 no NetworkPolicy (MEDIUM),","-F4 mutable image tag / no digest pin (LOW).","+### Policies / parameters","+- Policies: **none** defined on `/` or `/app` (user or operator).","+- Runtime parameters: **none** per-vhost.","+- Global parameters: only `internal_cluster_id` (system-managed)."," ","+### Queues","+| vhost | queue | type | durable | arguments |","+|-------|-------|------|---------|-----------|","+| `/app` | `app-queue` | classic | true | (none) |","+| `/` | (none) | | | |","+","+### Notable feature flags (all enabled)","+`quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`,","+`classic_queue_type_delivery_support`, `user_limits`, `feature_flags_v2`,","+`maintenance_mode_status`, plus the standard 3.12 set.","+"," ---"," ","-## 2. Planned Changes (what to change)","+## 2. Upgrade Target & Rationale"," ","-C1 [Upgrade/F4] Bump apache/spark:3.5.3 -> next approved patch (latest 3.5.x),","-   pinned by digest @sha256:... Apply uniformly to master, worker, and Job template.","-C2 [Security/F1] Add restricted securityContext to all three workloads:","-   runAsNonRoot: true, runAsUser: <non-zero>, allowPrivilegeEscalation: false,","-   readOnlyRootFilesystem: true (emptyDir for /tmp + spark work dirs),","-   capabilities.drop: [ALL], seccompProfile.type: RuntimeDefault.","-C3 [RBAC/F2] Reconcile Role to declared manifest: remove out-of-band \"pods\" and","-   trim write verbs (delete/update/patch) not needed by the SparkPi batch job;","-   re-apply from version control to stop drift.","-C4 [Network/F3] Add default-deny NetworkPolicy + explicit allows for","-   worker->master 7077 and operator access to UI 8080/8081.","-C5 [Hygiene] Set automountServiceAccountToken: false where the token is not","-   needed; confirm unused \"default\" SA stays unused.","+Recommend a **two-step major upgrade**: 3.12.14 → latest 3.13.x → 4.0.x.","+RabbitMQ does not support skipping a minor series for online/rolling upgrades,","+so 3.12 → 3.13 must precede any move to 4.x."," ","+| Step | From | To | Why |","+|------|------|----|----|","+| 1 | 3.12.14 | latest 3.13.x | Required stepping stone; surfaces 4.0 deprecation warnings; Khepri available as preview. |","+| 2 | 3.13.x | latest 4.0.x | Target release; classic mirrored queues fully removed, `queue_master_locator` removed. |","+","+### Compatibility blockers to resolve BEFORE step 2 (4.0)","+1. **Classic mirrored queues are removed in 4.0.** None are currently in use","+   (no HA policy, `app-queue` is plain classic), but the","+   `classic_mirrored_queue_version` flag is enabled. Confirm no mirrored queues","+   exist at change time and migrate any to **quorum queues**.","+2. **`queue_master_locator` is removed in 4.0**, replaced by","+   `queue_leader_locator` (`balanced` / `client-local`). Update","+   `rabbitmq-config` accordingly (`queue_leader_locator = balanced`).","+3. **Erlang version:** 4.0 requires Erlang 26+. The `rabbitmq:4.0-management`","+   image bundles a compatible OTP, so the image bump handles this.","+4. **Feature flags:** all required flags must be `enabled` before each upgrade.","+   Current set is fully enabled — re-verify after step 1 and run","+   `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`.","+"," ---"," ","-## 3. Order of Execution (lowest-risk first)","+## 3. Configuration Migration Items"," ","-1. C4 NetworkPolicy (additive; apply default-deny last) — validate connectivity.","-2. C3 RBAC reconcile — confirm Job still runs under reduced permissions.","-3. C2 securityContext hardening — rolling restart of master/worker.","-4. C1 image upgrade — rolling update master/worker, then re-run Job.","-5. C5 SA token hygiene — final tightening.","+| Current | Action in change window | Notes |","+|---------|------------------------|-------|","+| `app-queue` (classic, durable) | Evaluate migration to **quorum queue** | Quorum queues require redeclaration; cannot convert in place. Drain → redeclare → repoint clients, or shadow-queue cutover. |","+| No HA policy | Add quorum-queue-based redundancy policy if HA is desired | Do NOT add classic mirroring (deprecated/removed). |","+| `app-user` permissions `.* .* .*` on `/app` | Tighten to least privilege | Optional hardening; restrict configure/write/read regexes to what the app needs. |","+| `queue_master_locator = min-masters` | Replace with `queue_leader_locator = balanced` | Apply at the 3.13→4.0 step. |","+| No resource requests/limits | Set CPU/memory requests + limits on the STS | Improves scheduling/QoS stability during rolling restarts. |","+| Memory/disk watermarks (defaults) | Review `vm_memory_high_watermark` | Defaults acceptable; revisit under load. |"," ","-Rationale: apply isolation and least-privilege before the version bump so the","-upgrade is validated against the hardened baseline; keep the version change last","-and easiest to roll back.","+---"," ","+## 4. Execution Procedure (for the scheduled change window)","+","+Rolling, one node at a time. StatefulSet updates highest ordinal first; use a","+controlled `RollingUpdate` (or `OnDelete`) and verify each node rejoins before","+the next.","+","+1. **Pre-checks**","+   - `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` — 3/3 running, no alarms, no partitions.","+   - `rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app` — confirm queue types.","+   - Export definitions: `rabbitmqctl export_definitions definitions.json`","+     (or `rabbitmqadmin export`). Store off-cluster.","+   - Verify all feature flags enabled.","+2. **Bump image** in StatefulSet from `rabbitmq:3.12-management` to the 3.13","+   target (step 1), later to `rabbitmq:4.0-management` (step 2).","+3. **Rolling restart**: per node, drain (`rabbitmqctl upgrade drain` /","+   maintenance mode), let the pod restart on the new image, wait until it","+   rejoins and syncs (`rabbitmqctl await_online_quorum_plus_one`, check","+   `cluster_status`) before proceeding.","+4. **Post step-1**: `rabbitmqctl enable_feature_flag all`; verify no 4.0","+   deprecation warnings in logs.","+5. **Between steps**: update `rabbitmq-config` (`queue_leader_locator`), migrate","+   `app-queue` to quorum if chosen, apply any new policies.","+6. **Step 2 (4.0)**: repeat image bump + rolling restart.","+"," ---"," ","-## 4. Verification Per Step","+## 5. Validation (post-upgrade)"," ","-- C4: kubectl get netpol -n spark-pi; worker logs show registration to","-  spark://spark-master:7077; master 8080 UI reachable only from allowed source.","-- C3: kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi <verb> <res>","-  -n spark-pi matches intended matrix; re-run Job -> Completed.","-- C2: kubectl get pod -o jsonpath shows runAsNonRoot/dropped caps; pods Running 1/1;","-  no CrashLoop.","-- C1: kubectl get deploy -o jsonpath='{..image}' shows new digest; kubectl rollout","-  status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi; re-run spark-pi Job,","-  expect log \"Pi is roughly 3.14...\" and exit 0.","+- `rabbitmqctl status` on each node → expected version, no errors.","+- `rabbitmqctl cluster_status` → 3 running nodes, no partitions, no alarms.","+- `rabbitmqctl list_vhosts` → `/`, `/app` present.","+- `rabbitmqctl list_users` → `admin` (administrator), `app-user`.","+- `rabbitmqctl list_permissions -p /app` → unchanged (or tightened per plan).","+- `rabbitmqctl list_queues -p /app` → `app-queue` present and reachable.","+- Publish/consume smoke test against `/app` with `app-user`.","+- Management UI (port 15672) reachable; `loopback_users.guest = false` honored."," "," ---"," ","-## 5. Rollback","+## 6. Rollback"," ","-Each change applied from version-controlled manifests; rollback = kubectl rollout","-undo (deployments) or re-apply previous manifest (Role, NetworkPolicy, Job). Take a","-kubectl get all,role,rolebinding,netpol -o yaml snapshot before the window.","-backoffLimit=0 means a failed verification Job run must be deleted and re-created,","-not auto-retried.","+- **Definitions backup** from step 1 is the recovery artifact.","+- RabbitMQ does **not** support in-place downgrade. Rollback = redeploy the","+  previous image on a fresh data dir and import exported definitions, OR restore","+  from a volume snapshot taken pre-upgrade.","+- **Take a PV/PVC snapshot of all three `rabbitmq-N` volumes immediately before","+  each step** — the only reliable rollback for mnesia/Khepri state.","+- Abort criteria: a node fails to rejoin within SLA, persistent partition, or","+  queue data loss → halt, restore snapshot, re-import definitions."," "," ---"," ","-## 6. Approval","+## 7. Risks"," ","-This plan must be reviewed and signed off before any kubectl apply is executed.","-No item above has been applied; the live spark-pi namespace remains exactly as","-inspected on 2026-06-18.","+| Risk | Mitigation |","+|------|-----------|","+| Skipping 3.13 → unsupported 3.12→4.0 jump | Enforce two-step path. |","+| Classic→quorum migration drops messages | Drain queue first; shadow-queue cutover; low-traffic window. |","+| No resource limits → OOM during rolling restart | Set requests/limits before the window. |","+| Downgrade impossible | PV snapshots + definitions export before every step. |","+| Feature flags not fully enabled blocks upgrade | `enable_feature_flag all` and verify pre-step. |"]}],"originalFile":"# spark-pi Namespace — Migration & Upgrade Change Plan\n\nStatus: DRAFT FOR REVIEW — no changes have been applied. Live configuration is\nunchanged. Execution is deferred to an approved change window.\n\nDate: 2026-06-18  |  Scope: namespace spark-pi  |  Author: ops migration prep\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State (baseline, as inspected)\n\nWorkloads (all on image apache/spark:3.5.3, ServiceAccount spark-pi):\n\n- spark-master (Deployment): replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi; ports 7077,8080.\n- spark-worker (Deployment): replicas=1; req 200m/512Mi, lim 500m/1Gi;\n  env SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1.\n- spark-pi (Job): spark-submit --master local[2] --driver-memory 512m,\n  SparkPi partitions=1000, backoffLimit=0 (currently Completed).\n\nRBAC: Role spark-pi-role (LIVE verbs create/get/list/watch/delete/update/patch on\nservices, configmaps, persistentvolumeclaims, AND pods), RoleBinding\nspark-pi-role-binding -> SA spark-pi. SA \"default\" exists but is unused.\n\nConfigMaps: kube-root-ca.crt (system), config-audit (prior read-only audit).\nNetworkPolicies: none. securityContext: {} (empty) on all workloads.\n\nCarried findings from config-audit: F1 securityContext hardening missing (HIGH),\nF2 RBAC over-permission + drift on \"pods\" (MEDIUM), F3 no NetworkPolicy (MEDIUM),\nF4 mutable image tag / no digest pin (LOW).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Planned Changes (what to change)\n\nC1 [Upgrade/F4] Bump apache/spark:3.5.3 -> next approved patch (latest 3.5.x),\n   pinned by digest @sha256:... Apply uniformly to master, worker, and Job template.\nC2 [Security/F1] Add restricted securityContext to all three workloads:\n   runAsNonRoot: true, runAsUser: <non-zero>, allowPrivilegeEscalation: false,\n   readOnlyRootFilesystem: true (emptyDir for /tmp + spark work dirs),\n   capabilities.drop: [ALL], seccompProfile.type: RuntimeDefault.\nC3 [RBAC/F2] Reconcile Role to declared manifest: remove out-of-band \"pods\" and\n   trim write verbs (delete/update/patch) not needed by the SparkPi batch job;\n   re-apply from version control to stop drift.\nC4 [Network/F3] Add default-deny NetworkPolicy + explicit allows for\n   worker->master 7077 and operator access to UI 8080/8081.\nC5 [Hygiene] Set automountServiceAccountToken: false where the token is not\n   needed; confirm unused \"default\" SA stays unused.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Order of Execution (lowest-risk first)\n\n1. C4 NetworkPolicy (additive; apply default-deny last) — validate connectivity.\n2. C3 RBAC reconcile — confirm Job still runs under reduced permissions.\n3. C2 securityContext hardening — rolling restart of master/worker.\n4. C1 image upgrade — rolling update master/worker, then re-run Job.\n5. C5 SA token hygiene — final tightening.\n\nRationale: apply isolation and least-privilege before the version bump so the\nupgrade is validated against the hardened baseline; keep the version change last\nand easiest to roll back.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Verification Per Step\n\n- C4: kubectl get netpol -n spark-pi; worker logs show registration to\n  spark://spark-master:7077; master 8080 UI reachable only from allowed source.\n- C3: kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi <verb> <res>\n  -n spark-pi matches intended matrix; re-run Job -> Completed.\n- C2: kubectl get pod -o jsonpath shows runAsNonRoot/dropped caps; pods Running 1/1;\n  no CrashLoop.\n- C1: kubectl get deploy -o jsonpath='{..image}' shows new digest; kubectl rollout\n  status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi; re-run spark-pi Job,\n  expect log \"Pi is roughly 3.14...\" and exit 0.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback\n\nEach change applied from version-controlled manifests; rollback = kubectl rollout\nundo (deployments) or re-apply previous manifest (Role, NetworkPolicy, Job). Take a\nkubectl get all,role,rolebinding,netpol -o yaml snapshot before the window.\nbackoffLimit=0 means a failed verification Job run must be deleted and re-created,\nnot auto-retried.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Approval\n\nThis plan must be reviewed and signed off before any kubectl apply is executed.\nNo item above has been applied; the live spark-pi namespace remains exactly as\ninspected on 2026-06-18.\n","userModified":false}}
