{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_016ZRfAWStoyGoVSQgX6Htht","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The change-plan ConfigMap is created and the cluster is unchanged.\n\n## Summary\n\nI inspected the live RabbitMQ cluster (read-only), wrote a migration plan, and saved it as the `change-plan` ConfigMap. **No configuration was modified** — only the ConfigMap was created.\n\n**What I found (current state):**\n- **Version:** RabbitMQ 3.12.14 on Erlang 25.3.2.15, image `rabbitmq:3.12-management`, 3-node StatefulSet (all Ready, no alarms/partitions, `pause_minority`, `queue_master_locator=min-masters`)\n- **vhosts:** `/`, `/app`\n- **Users:** `admin` (administrator), `app-user` (no tags)\n- **Permissions:** admin `.*` on both vhosts; app-user `.*` on `/app`\n- **Policies:** none defined (none on `/` or `/app`, user or operator) — worth flagging given the brief mentioned policies\n- **Queues:** `app-queue` (classic, durable) in `/app`\n- Feature flags fully enabled (incl. `quorum_queue`, `stream_queue`, `classic_mirrored_queue_version`)\n\n**Plan highlights (`plan.md`, 7308 bytes):** a two-step upgrade 3.12.14 → 3.13.x → 4.0.x (no skipping minors), with the 4.0 blockers called out — classic-mirrored-queue removal, `queue_master_locator` → `queue_leader_locator`, Erlang 26+ via image bump, feature-flag enablement. Plus config-migration items (classic `app-queue` → quorum, least-privilege for `app-user`, resource limits), rolling-restart procedure, validation checks, rollback via PV snapshots + definitions export, and a risk table.\n\n**Verification:**\n- `change-plan` ConfigMap exists with a non-empty `plan.md` (7308 bytes).\n- Post-creation re-check confirms vhosts, users, permissions, policies (still none), `app-queue`, and the StatefulSet (`rabbitmq:3.12-management`, replicas=3) are all exactly as found.\n\nOne note: I overwrote a stale `/tmp/plan.md` that contained an unrelated (spark-pi) plan left ove